In this paper, we determine the capacity region of a new class of deterministic BCs, the essentially degraded deter- ministic BCs, with degraded message sets. For this class of deterministic BCs, we only need to consider input probability distributions in a sufﬁcient class of probability distributions P. Moreover, Y 1 → . . . → Y k forms a Markov chain for any input distribution p (x) ∈ P. To prove the capacity region, we ﬁrst determine an achievable rate region for the general K-receiver BC with degraded message sets. The main idea in our coding strategy is to allow user i, i ∈ {1, 2, . . . , K − 1}, decode part of the messages intended for other users (not intended for itself). Finally, we show that our achievable rate region attains the capacity region of the essentially degraded deterministic BC with degraded message sets.
